tion"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-d1dcd849 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--6"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e3d1dcd8" id="" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 id="" data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-b89cfa18"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-3db89cfa">What Exactly Is Glucosamine? </span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-18e3d1dc"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-fa18e3d1">Glucosamine may be best designed as a natural amino based sugar that is organically produced in your system. This is often used as a dietary supplement and doctors consider it an excellent alternative treatment solution for osteoarthritis and any other form of joint pain. In its essentially natural form, this amino sugar may be found around the joint and cartilage area where it assumes the structure of certain chemical compounds that are tailored to improve joint function. 
<br>
<br>These supplements are usually processed from your crustacean shells. In some instances, it may also be produced by the fermentation of bacteria around the grains. You will find most of these supplements in multiple forms like capsules, gels, and tablets. In some instances, they may also be available in the form of juice mixes. 
<br>
<br>When it comes to glucosamine supplements, you will find two popular categories namely, the sulfate and hydrochloride variants of the product. According to several studies, glucosamine supplements boost the production of cartilage in your joint area. Certain studies have further suggested that taking these supplements may also cut down the breakdown of collagen which further goes a long way in treating joint pain. 
<br>
